        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 6:24PM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 624 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 9 miles northeast of Ralph to near Sorum.
Movement was east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lodgepole, Sorum, Prairie City, and Date.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
